== Projects

=== Patent Analyzer  #sub[Python, Django, OpenAI, TogetherAI, QdrantDB, Selenium]
- As a Final Year Project, my team and I implemented a patent document analyzer on TRIZ principles using a decoder LLM model.
- I implemented most backend components such as; automated text extraction using bs4, Chain of thought prompting, and hybrid RAG search through qdrantDB.
- Developed and adapted a manual classification method into chain-of-thoughts and modified vector search method.
- Delivered a deployable patent analysis platform capable of structured, principle-based insights from raw patent documents.

=== Autonomous Expense Agent #sub[Python, Gemini 3, Agentic MCP, AWS, YOLO, MongoDB]
- Architected a **multi-agent multimodal system** using Google ADK, implementing structured output parsing and stateful artifact management for long-running financial workflows.
- Integrated **Model Context Protocol (MCP)** to unify tool functions across MongoDB transactions, Matplotlib data visualization, and Google Cloud Storage (Blob).
- Developed a **YOLO-based computer vision pipeline** to crop and pre-process receipt images, optimizing OCR accuracy and reducing downstream LLM token consumption.
- Deployed a Telegram-bot interface supporting MarkdownV2, real-time typing indicators, and multimodal data ingestion.
- *Upcoming*: Orchestrating a fine-tuning pipeline for **Gemma 3 (GemmaFunction)** to transition the agent to a privacy-centric, self-hosted open-source model.

=== Big Data File Processing of IoT Data #sub[PySpark, Kafka, Zookeeper, MongoDB, Matplotlib]
- Designed and implemented a data warehouse schema in MongoDB for IoT data, defining collection relationships and an upsert strategy.
- Built a Kafka Pub/Sub system to ingest and process real-time streams from three distinct IoT sources.
- Used PySpark for real-time preprocessing, transformation, and custom anomaly detection via User-Defined Functions (UDFs).
- Persisted processed and joined data back into MongoDB and used change streams to trigger dynamic visualizations with Matplotlib.

